# Repository Rules

Keep the repository clean, predictable and easy to maintain.

## Project structure

Use a clear backend structure:

app/
- main.py
- api/
- core/
- db/
- models/
- schemas/
- services/

tests/
- test_*.py

scripts/
- utility scripts only

## Architecture

- Keep route handlers thin.
- Put business logic in services.
- Put database models in models.
- Put request/response validation in schemas.
- Put configuration in core/settings.py.
- Put database connection/session logic in db/.
- Avoid large files with mixed responsibilities.

## Maintainability

- Prefer simple readable code.
- Use explicit names.
- Do not add abstractions too early.
- Avoid duplicated logic.
- Avoid hardcoded config.
- Keep changes small and reviewable.

## Environment

- Use .env for local secrets.
- Keep .env out of git.
- Provide .env.example with safe placeholder values.

## Dependencies

- Do not add new dependencies without a clear reason.
- Prefer standard library when enough.
- Keep requirements.txt updated.

## Documentation

Update README when changing:
- setup
- commands
- environment variables
- deployment
- project structure
